subject: resource/Neue_Staatsgalerie
object: The Neue Staatsgalerie in Stuttgart, Germany, was designed by the British firm James Stirling, Michael Wilford and Associates, although largely accredited solely to partner James Stirling.  It was constructed in the 1970s and opened to the public in 1984. The building has been claimed as the epitome of Post-modernism.
